<subSubSection id="362ADBB2A4429E61403CD27F09C87C44" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9DAA668B3F9D4A505CD35052B9A49669" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1DC5379E5D260FCE65B702C34E12078F" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
In the discriminant function analysis, the Awashima specimen was classified as 
<taxonomicName id="89F45508AB72F4ACEBC394E690982E65" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="905AC76E0BFDCC4CECBB461B2E1730C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. On the scatterplots of the first two canonical variates, the specimen was located outside of, but close to, the area of 
<taxonomicName id="9EF0B3866215967723494C2F21859EE8" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="E309CD90CAD46B86C264281D83DE520B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BCC3059ABC5D1AE59177F5733CF2519A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Scatterplot of the first two canonical variates obtained from the discriminant analysis of four measurements of the female pronotum." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.43.80969.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690342" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">3</figureCitation>
). These results suggest that the Awashima specimen is most similar in external morphology to, but different from, 
<taxonomicName id="82CD426A49518429632A796E8BD65BA9" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="71E40F6A574E7D62E5F221B87459B8D8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Differences between the Awashima specimen and 
<taxonomicName id="57B8244C9478B91355DDCF070B05CD40" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="49BD65F3887112CFF8243D1E28EFB4E0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were also observed in other morphological features: the body length of the Awashima specimen (see below) is smaller than that of 
<taxonomicName id="1E34A7ADFAF151C68C47E686075736EF" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="178912D2829573A8092022D3375D972B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(n=6 from Mt. Yahikosan; BLm 15.32-14.35, mean 14.94 mm; BLl 14.22-13.46, mean 13.73 mm; BLc 13.64-12.89, mean 13.18 mm) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5B70EA9A1118BD1BAD9AC3ABBD1D4646" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pterostichus awashimaensis sp. nov. holotype female (A, C, E) and P. yahikosanus female from Mt. Yahikosan (B, D, F) A, B habitus dorsal view C, D pronotum dorsal view E, F vagina anterior view. am, apophysis of the median oviduct; as, apophysis of the seminal canal; m, median oviduct; p, pigmentation on the innermost part of the vagina; sp, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.43.80969.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690343" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4A, B</figureCitation>
); in the pronotum, anterior angles are barely produced, hind angles are obtuse, and posterior margin is arcuate posteriorly behind the laterobasal impressions in the Awashima specimen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1BFD200BF769F1C36C0735B85D82038B" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pterostichus awashimaensis sp. nov. holotype female (A, C, E) and P. yahikosanus female from Mt. Yahikosan (B, D, F) A, B habitus dorsal view C, D pronotum dorsal view E, F vagina anterior view. am, apophysis of the median oviduct; as, apophysis of the seminal canal; m, median oviduct; p, pigmentation on the innermost part of the vagina; sp, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.43.80969.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690343" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4C</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="11DE30881B0BDF91F09C3C9B3FB22824" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="FC05D1F7E9A48CBE0A24B2BE8DF3548A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, anterior angles are notably produced, hind angles are right-angled to acute, and the posterior margin behind the laterobasal impressions is almost straight (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BCD3FD73DB5D2415BFC9D8CD62429039" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pterostichus awashimaensis sp. nov. holotype female (A, C, E) and P. yahikosanus female from Mt. Yahikosan (B, D, F) A, B habitus dorsal view C, D pronotum dorsal view E, F vagina anterior view. am, apophysis of the median oviduct; as, apophysis of the seminal canal; m, median oviduct; p, pigmentation on the innermost part of the vagina; sp, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.43.80969.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690343" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4D</figureCitation>
); the body of the Awashima specimen is darker than that of 
<taxonomicName id="1292CF5F42588B8B31B64C7EB968C956" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="82573C9DE887AE87DF74C4F8ACC7AFA5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9B7F10E34B23E5ACB0E46C99BAD5C91E" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pterostichus awashimaensis sp. nov. holotype female (A, C, E) and P. yahikosanus female from Mt. Yahikosan (B, D, F) A, B habitus dorsal view C, D pronotum dorsal view E, F vagina anterior view. am, apophysis of the median oviduct; as, apophysis of the seminal canal; m, median oviduct; p, pigmentation on the innermost part of the vagina; sp, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.43.80969.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690343" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4A-D</figureCitation>
); and pigmentation on the innermost part of vagina is smaller in the Awashima specimen, less than half the size of median and seminal apophyses (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A46E9DFD8C197D212B6F6E3C72550241" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pterostichus awashimaensis sp. nov. holotype female (A, C, E) and P. yahikosanus female from Mt. Yahikosan (B, D, F) A, B habitus dorsal view C, D pronotum dorsal view E, F vagina anterior view. am, apophysis of the median oviduct; as, apophysis of the seminal canal; m, median oviduct; p, pigmentation on the innermost part of the vagina; sp, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.43.80969.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690343" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4E</figureCitation>
), while it is larger than these apophyses in 
<taxonomicName id="A46A87175ADA1C13AE0F1EFEBF8FDE39" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="FF30ED7AA55095B23E3187C28828E44B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="540CE83B121A0494F205AC364FA4C4DF" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pterostichus awashimaensis sp. nov. holotype female (A, C, E) and P. yahikosanus female from Mt. Yahikosan (B, D, F) A, B habitus dorsal view C, D pronotum dorsal view E, F vagina anterior view. am, apophysis of the median oviduct; as, apophysis of the seminal canal; m, median oviduct; p, pigmentation on the innermost part of the vagina; sp, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.43.80969.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690343" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4F</figureCitation>
). In the 
<taxonomicName id="97886DFF56B8D00C231A729EBE73E060" authorityName="Sasakawa &amp; Itô" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterostichus macrogenys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrogenys">
<emphasis id="9560AC4FEE4DFCF306A832793B75E557" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Pterostichus macrogenys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, pronotum shape and the pigmentation on the innermost part of vagina differ distinctly among species and are used as important species-level diagnostic characters (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="4401419131B0C140C00659944B4B05FE" author="Sasakawa, K" journalOrPublisher="Biogeography" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="69 - 78" refId="B12" refString="Sasakawa, K, 2005. Pterostichus macrogenys Bates, 1883 (Coleoptera, Carabidae) and its allied species of northern Japan. Biogeography 7: 69 - 78" title="Pterostichus macrogenys Bates, 1883 (Coleoptera, Carabidae) and its allied species of northern Japan." volume="7" year="2005">Sasakawa 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C80A66722529558496F95E12419BB9B7" author="Sugimura, A" journalOrPublisher="Elytra" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="641 - 647" refId="B20" refString="Sugimura, A, 2005. A new species of the genus Pterostichus (Coleoptera, Carabidae) from Mt. Fukube-ga-take, Chuno District of Gifu Prefecture, central Japan. Elytra 33: 641 - 647" title="A new species of the genus Pterostichus (Coleoptera, Carabidae) from Mt. Fukube-ga-take, Chuno District of Gifu Prefecture, central Japan." volume="33" year="2005">Sugimura 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="873015A9FE33DD892DDCAC7F4E8AAD8A" author="Morita, S" journalOrPublisher="Elytra New Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="9 - 17" refId="B7" refString="Morita, S, Ohkawa, H, Kurihara, T, 2013. Two new macrocephalic pterostichine carabids (Coleoptera, Carabidae) from central Japan. Elytra New Series 3: 9 - 17" title="Two new macrocephalic pterostichine carabids (Coleoptera, Carabidae) from central Japan." volume="3" year="2013">Morita et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Because these characters differ distinctly between the Awashima specimen and 
<taxonomicName id="5841CBE8FC6F4789AC0C2C479E46DD8F" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="409CE8CA72512ACF0A922A47DEADDA7E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we describe the Awashima specimen as a new species. Based on information on the morphological features of the pronotum and female genitalia in related species (
<bibRefCitation id="16930539211DDAED3846A0EA44BA03DC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3390/insects11110803" author="Sasakawa, K" journalOrPublisher="Applied Entomology and Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refId="B17" refString="Sasakawa, K, Mitsuduka, Y, Ito, H, 2020. Unexpected species identities and interspecific relationships in a subterranean beetle lineage, the Pterostichus macrogenys species group (Coleoptera, Carabidae), revealed by fine-scale field sampling and detailed morphological comparisons. Insects 11: 803. https://doi.org/10.3390/insects11110803" title="Unexpected species identities and interspecific relationships in a subterranean beetle lineage, the Pterostichus macrogenys species group (Coleoptera, Carabidae), revealed by fine-scale field sampling and detailed morphological comparisons. Insects 11: 803." url="https://doi.org/10.3390/insects11110803" year="2020">Sasakawa et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
and references therein), notably produced pronotal anterior angles and developed vaginal pigmentation are limited to some species and considered to be derived character states in the 
<taxonomicName id="A097AE03E58266621233B32A9C94B057" authorityName="Sasakawa &amp; Itô" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterostichus macrogenys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrogenys">
<emphasis id="45E3F37B47AB6531F6F06598D8195C4B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Pterostichus macrogenys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. Therefore, the Awashima species is considered more ancestral than 
<taxonomicName id="B24EBEA6F57B725CDA7C8AB9D0686791" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. yahikosanus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yahikosanus">
<emphasis id="8BF0267EFB412FB3A45B83A9E4A220B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. yahikosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with respect to the pronotal and genital features.
</paragraph>
